node.text: I have lived in Peabody (north of Boston), Hartford, Houston, and NYC. I’ve played just about every sport. I am black and white. I am a woman. I lift heavy ass weights. I was a school teacher. I am a dog mama. I am so happy with my life experiences because they have helped me relate to and connect with SO many DIFFERENT people, and that’s what keeps my life so fulfilling and fun. That’s what fuels me. Never forget where you came from and never burn your bridges - my AAU coaches always instilled this in all of their players and I’m forever grateful, and I am EXTRA thankful for @necntv  @nbcsboston and the lovely @_hannah.donnelly for giving me the opportunity to share my story in MA - where it all began 🥰 If you’re looking for the longer version, check out the link in my bio!

node.title: Never forget where you came from!

node.text: To say this partnership is meaningful would be the BIGGEST understatement of the century! Here is a litttttle bit of the backstory of my journey with @reebok - it is an honor and a privilege to be part of the family. I cannot wait to share all the big things that we have in store for y’all!! Get ready to feel empowered, embrace your inner athlete and embody exactly what it means to be part of a team!

node.text: I’m finally doing it y’all 😭 so I’ve been talking about mantra walls for a while now, and now each weekish I will share one with you! Mantras help me feel unstuck and empower me to take control over my circumstances. Having them on a wall really helps because they’re always present and serve as a “quick visual menu” in times where I can’t think of them. Hope this helps 🥰 sending y’all love!

node.text: It was an absolute honor to spend time with my girl @kellyripa and @ryanseacrest where I got to show them two of my fave workouts - the Tabata and the EMOM 😈🤗 We are almost to February, so now’s the time to give yourself feedback on the first three weeks of January - have you been doing what you said you wanted to do before you got tired, busy, distracted, etc.? Try these two workouts out - you don’t need a ton of time or equipment! Huge shout out to @wiener_jan and @denisemariekelly for making this happen with @livekellyandryan and huge thank you to Y’ALL for supporting me always ❤️❤️❤️

node.text:
Y’all should have seen the full Sienna Grace before and after @kristinmcgee FAMILY meditation (thank you, Kristin!!!!) We are SO excited to offer new family classes every week of December, including FOUR new classes from me today (and four more coming later this month 🤗). When I created these classes I had three simple goals in mind, to get kids:
1️⃣ to learn a little
2️⃣ to move a lot and
3️⃣ to fall in love with exercise!
The Brain Breaks are five minutes that are awesome by themselves in between virtual learning classes, the Fit Funs are 15min beginner level with a muscle of the day and movement of the day and a game, and the Fit Strongs are 20min more intermediate level like a PE class. Let me know your favorites below 🤗
shout out @mr.1600 for the video!

node.text:
I always go on IG live after I teach, but last night was different. At the end, I mentioned that I was having an off day full of anxious thoughts, overwhelm and uncontrollables that was giving me a run for my money. I asked what y’all do when you feel like this and you gave AMAZING advice and I couldn’t not share in case anyone else is in need (I have a feeling I’m not alone in these thoughts, especially given the time and space we are in). So I will share some here, but PLEASE add what works for you so others can benefit. Thanks for being there for me last night and always 🖤 today is already feeling better and brighter!
▪️clean/de clutter with loud music
▪️write down all the things in your head on paper to get it all out and then go back line by line
▪️remember there’s a solution for everything but it’s not always your responsibility to figure the solution out
▪️call a friend and LAUGH
▪️meditation
▪️name it and say how you’re feeling out loud
▪️work with a therapist and/or life coach
▪️workout
▪️come up with a mantra to keep you centered and to prevent snowballing
▪️help someone else to get out of your own way/head
Sending you all so much love,  compassion for yourselves and a friendly reminder that you’re not alone 🖤

node.text: There were soooo many first timers on tonight’s bike bootcamp 😍😍😍…first of many to come! You’re officially stuck with me, so let me know your leaderboard name below and how you surprised yourself with your own damn strength during class tonight - we’re a family now 🤗🥰 #mondaymayhem

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by JESS SIMS in Peloton. May be an image of 1 person and indoor.

node.text: Oh how I look forward to #mondaymayhem 🤗🤗🤗 after taking Sundays completely off to rest my body and mind, I am sooo ready for a tough workout on Monday. I’ve always been drawn toward teaching and taking classes that have a set number of intervals where you just WORK. You just GO. No BS, no changes in the programming to distract you, just you against you time after time. THAT is where the mental breakthroughs happen - when you stay so fully present on the challenge at hand that nothing else matters in that moment. It’s easy to do your best once, but can you do it 5x? 10x? 15x? Or in this class, 33x lol 🥴 Proud of y’all tonight, and always remember - the “boring” is where you get BETTER.

node.text: Hard to believe that this is real. When I played my last basketball game in 2010 I thought I had to leave the sport I had dedicated my life to - my team, the practices, the uniform, the pasta dinners (if you know you know), everything. So to have this opportunity to get back to the sport that gave me so much is the ultimate honor. I’ve been to two of the six games this season @barclayscenter and have watched the rest on tv and I can’t explain the level of joy that the @nyliberty team has already given to me. Watching these amazingly talented women has inspired me more than you could possibly imagine...how they celebrate one another, how they show up, their heart, their hustle...LET’S GO NEW YORK!!!! 🖤🗽I start this Saturday at 2pm, see y’all there!!! #ownthecrown #nyliberty #wnba

node.text:
Rehearsal dinner photo dump 🤪
Like many, I haven’t seen my siblings in so long, and I can’t think of a better way to reunite than with my little sister’s wedding! There’s 6 years between my sister and I and 21 months between my brother and I. Between my brother controlling the radio on the way to school (woof) and my sister requiring babysitting (how was it ALWAYS my turn?!), we definitely had our regular sibling ups and downs as kids, but I’m so happy that adulthood has brought us infinitely closer. Love them so much 🖤 wedding day photos to come!! PS - my mom spilled a full glass of red wine on my dress right before these photos were taken 🥴 you’re welcome.
